<item>
            <title>[SOLR-892] PHPResponseWriter fails to serialize boolean vars for spellcheck output</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-892</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When using org.apache.solr.request.PHPSerializedResponseWriter as the queryResponseWriter, search results that contain spellcheck-fields are incorrectly serialized and can&apos;t be properly deserialized by PHP 5. Example error:&lt;br/&gt;
Notice: unserialize() &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;function.unserialize&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;: Error at offset 305 of 312 bytes in /Solr/Client.php on line 131 &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;How to reproduce:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;open the example solrconfig.xml (apache-solr-nightly/example/solr/conf/solrconfig.xml)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;uncomment the PHPSerializedResponseWriter, around line 733&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;start the Jetty container&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;index all the example documents from exampledocs/&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;open this URL: &lt;a href=&quot;http://localhost:8983/solr/spellCheckCompRH?cmd=&amp;amp;q=ipod&amp;amp;spellcheck=true&amp;amp;spellcheck.extendedResults=true&amp;amp;spellcheck.onlyMorePopular=true&amp;amp;wt=phps&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://localhost:8983/solr/spellCheckCompRH?cmd=&amp;amp;q=ipod&amp;amp;spellcheck=true&amp;amp;spellcheck.extendedResults=true&amp;amp;spellcheck.onlyMorePopular=true&amp;amp;wt=phps&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;At the very end of the serialized array you will see this:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; s:10:&quot;spellcheck&quot;;a:1:{s:11:&quot;suggestions&quot;;a:1:&lt;/p&gt;
{s:16:&quot;correctlySpelled&quot;;true}
&lt;p&gt;}} &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When you serialize a similar array in PHP, you get this:&lt;br/&gt;
echo serialize(array(&quot;spellcheck&quot;=&amp;gt;array(&quot;suggestions&quot;=&amp;gt;array(&quot;correctlySpelled&quot;=&amp;gt;true))));&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; a:1:{s:10:&quot;spellcheck&quot;;a:1:{s:11:&quot;suggestions&quot;;a:1:&lt;/p&gt;
{s:16:&quot;correctlySpelled&quot;;b:1;}
&lt;p&gt;}} &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So it seems to be, that the PHPResponseWriter doesn&apos;t recognize &quot;true&quot; to be a boolean var and prints it directly, instead of transforming it to &quot;b:1;&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Solr nightly 2008-11-25, example configuration, Jetty container&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
